HEADWORD: Jeweler
<hw>Jew"el*er</hw> <pr>(j⟦umac⟧"⟦ecr⟧l*l⟦etil⟧r <it>or</it>
j⟦udd⟧"⟦ecr⟧l*l⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>joaillier</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who makes, or deals in, jewels,
precious stones, and similar ornaments.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>jeweller</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Jeweler's gold</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Gold</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jewellery</ent>⟦br⟧
